  <summary date="2015-07-16T04:00:00Z" status="Introduced in Senate">Davis-Bacon Repeal Act

 Repeals the Davis-Bacon Act (which requires that the locally prevailing wage rate be paid to various classes of laborers and mechanics working under federally-financed or federally-assisted contracts for construction, alteration, and repair of public buildings or public works).

States that references in any law to a wage requirement of the Davis-Bacon Act shall be null and void.</summary>
